com.twilio.chat

Interface ChannelListener


  • public interface ChannelListener
    Listener interface to report channel operations such as member join/leave and messages add/delete/update.

    You should create this listener and attach it to channel using Channel.addListener() if you want to receive status updates on channel changes.

    This listener's callbacks will be called on the originating thread if it has a Looper, otherwise on the main UI thread. To invoke listener callbacks on a specific thread, wrap your call in a Handler invocation with a specific thread `someOtherThread` e.g. ```java Handler handler = new Handler(someOtherThreadLooper); handler.post(new Runnable() {

        void onMessageUpdated(Message message,

        Called when a Message is changed in the channel the current user is subscribed to.

        You could obtain the Channel where it was changed by using Message#getChannel() or Message#getChannelSid().

        Message change events include @link Message#getMessageBody() body @endlink updates and @link Message#getAttributes() attribute @endlink updates.

        Parameters:

      • onTypingEnded

        void onTypingEnded(Channel channel,
                   Member member)
        Called when an Member stops typing in a Channel.

        Typing indicator has a timeout after user stops typing to avoid triggering it too often. Expect about 5 seconds delay between stopping typing and receiving typing ended event.

        Parameters:
        channel - Channel on which the event happened.
        member - The member that stopped typing.
        See Also:
        onTypingStarted(com.twilio.chat.Channel, com.twilio.chat.Member)
